definition.value: An amino-acid betaine that is butanoate substituted with a hydroxy group at position C-3 and a trimethylammonium group at C-4.
An aralkylglucosinolic acid that consists of 1-thio-beta-D-glucopyranose attached to a 2-phenyl-N-(sulfooxy)ethanimidoyl group at the anomeric sulfur.
A dicarboxylic acid dianion obtained by the deprotonation of both the carboxy groups of adipic acid.
A berberine alkaloid isolated from  Corydalis saxicola.
